title: Population growth (annual %)
subtitle: The dataset shows annual population growth in % from 1961 to 2020
description: The annual population growth rate for year t is the exponential rate of growth of the midyear population from year t-1 to t, expressed as a percentage. Population is based on the de facto definition of population, which counts all residents regardless of legal status or citizenship.
